WEBVTT

01:16.958 --> 01:19.583
[somber music playing]

01:43.000 --> 01:44.916
[muffled singing]

01:45.000 --> 01:47.500
<i>♪ Keep your eyes</i>
<i>On your fellow man ♪</i>

01:51.375 --> 01:53.833
<i>♪ Old man Caesar</i>
<i>In his big empire ♪</i>

01:53.916 --> 01:56.958
<i>♪ Would just sit by</i>
<i>Still through higher</i>
<i>And higher ♪</i>

01:57.041 --> 02:01.000
<i>♪ Never had to worry</i>
<i>About a dime to spend ♪</i>

02:02.500 --> 02:05.375
<i>♪ He won the world</i>
<i>In a year or two ♪</i>

02:05.458 --> 02:07.833
<i>♪ Told everybody just</i>
<i>What to do ♪</i>

02:07.916 --> 02:09.500
<i>♪ But he sure found out ♪</i>

02:09.583 --> 02:12.083
<i>♪ Brutus wasn't his friend ♪</i>

02:13.333 --> 02:16.583
<i>♪ Well, that's it, Jack</i>
<i>Don't turn your back ♪</i>

02:16.666 --> 02:19.833
<i>♪ Don't you keep your mind</i>
<i>In a paper sack ♪</i>

02:19.916 --> 02:22.291
<i>♪ Just keep your eyes</i>
<i>On your fellow man ♪</i>

02:29.416 --> 02:30.708
Song was for you.

02:31.500 --> 02:32.916
Knew it was time
for your break.

02:37.125 --> 02:40.125
Take half.
It's all I got today.

02:43.875 --> 02:46.125
Been savin' up them nickels
you usually give me.

02:53.166 --> 02:55.458
You're like a cat.
You know that?

02:56.333 --> 02:58.375
Mysterious.

02:58.458 --> 03:00.541
Can't tell if you want
someone for petting

03:00.625 --> 03:01.958
or for scratching.

03:03.083 --> 03:05.166
Just getting familiar
with my surroundings.

03:05.250 --> 03:06.458
Where you from?

03:10.208 --> 03:11.375
Many places.

03:11.458 --> 03:12.916
Does the cat have a name?

03:17.708 --> 03:19.916
-Miranda.
-Miranda.

03:22.000 --> 03:23.541
Well, I could show you around.

03:23.625 --> 03:25.458
Take you to some new spots.

03:25.541 --> 03:26.875
We could dance a little?

03:27.583 --> 03:30.416
My favorite? The Blue Moon Bar.

03:30.500 --> 03:32.083
Best jukebox in town...

03:33.416 --> 03:35.958
maybe Saturday night?

03:39.541 --> 03:40.625
Sure.

03:52.958 --> 03:55.541
This is what I bought
with the nickels you give me.

03:57.791 --> 03:59.000
It's for you.

03:59.083 --> 04:01.083
Been waiting for you
to give me the time of day.

04:13.833 --> 04:15.500
Does this work on other girls?

04:15.583 --> 04:17.083
Is it working on you?

04:24.458 --> 04:25.875
[sighs] Uh...

04:28.291 --> 04:29.791
Oh, I'm sorry.

04:31.375 --> 04:33.291
Ah, nah.

04:33.375 --> 04:36.083
Been dreaming about this day,
just happy.

04:36.166 --> 04:37.625
Didn't mean no disrespect.

04:37.708 --> 04:39.083
Let me slow it down for you.

04:40.500 --> 04:41.833
Let's start over.

04:41.916 --> 04:42.916
Saturday night.

04:46.375 --> 04:47.333
Ah...

04:52.000 --> 04:53.291
I get off at 7:00.

05:07.958 --> 05:10.250
["Pictures of You" playing]

05:15.416 --> 05:17.125
[whirring]

05:20.041 --> 05:22.333
Uh, laundry day?

05:22.416 --> 05:23.833
Clara's getting married
and somehow,

05:23.916 --> 05:26.625
for the grace
of sweet baby Jesus,

05:26.708 --> 05:29.166
I scored a ticket.

05:29.250 --> 05:31.291
And you're going to wear
a T-shirt?

05:32.208 --> 05:34.708
Which will be fine. I mean...

05:34.791 --> 05:36.541
everyone will be looking
at the bride, anyway.

05:37.291 --> 05:39.916
["Pictures of You"
starts again]

05:40.000 --> 05:41.833
I'm having a hard time
picking one out.

05:41.916 --> 05:44.666
I'm going for the most clean
and least offensive.

05:44.750 --> 05:46.375
Tough choices.

05:46.458 --> 05:48.333
This is a solid collection.

05:48.416 --> 05:50.500
Jane picked them for me.
Who are you?

05:50.583 --> 05:51.541
I'm Miranda.

05:51.625 --> 05:54.333
Miranda? Didn't you jump
into a well?

05:54.416 --> 05:57.041
I did. I healed.

05:58.250 --> 06:00.125
Where's Jane?

06:00.208 --> 06:03.208
Resting. We took a trip
to our childhood home

06:03.291 --> 06:06.083
and I'm afraid
she was triggered.

06:06.166 --> 06:08.916
She had to climb
into an old well.
It was pretty rough.

06:09.000 --> 06:11.791
Oh. Okay. Tell her I said hey.

06:13.375 --> 06:14.541
Uh...

06:14.625 --> 06:17.333
Well, if everyone's going to be
looking at the bride...

06:18.333 --> 06:20.708
When your father
is a gigantic robot?

06:20.791 --> 06:22.041
That's a point.

06:24.583 --> 06:26.166
Miranda's awesome.

06:28.333 --> 06:31.583
-["Pictures of You" continues]
-[knock on door]

06:31.666 --> 06:36.458
Vic, you've been playing
this sad love song on repeat.

06:37.500 --> 06:38.250
[reduces volume]

06:38.333 --> 06:40.041
It's the only thing that helps.

06:42.666 --> 06:46.416
Everyone gets
their heart broken.

06:46.500 --> 06:48.791
I had mine broken
at least 16 times

06:48.875 --> 06:50.833
by the time I was your age.

06:52.708 --> 06:54.958
There's no superhuman strength

06:55.041 --> 06:56.875
that can save you
from heartache.

06:56.958 --> 06:58.250
I lost her.

07:00.458 --> 07:01.791
I'm a failure.

07:01.875 --> 07:03.666
You think you failed?

07:07.291 --> 07:10.458
I had a shot to stop Roni,
just like you.

07:11.708 --> 07:15.916
And I completely froze.

07:16.666 --> 07:18.041
Like an idiot.

07:19.041 --> 07:20.125
[sighs]

07:21.208 --> 07:23.875
Cliff is leaving for
his daughter's wedding.

07:23.958 --> 07:25.583
We need to say good-bye.

07:26.583 --> 07:29.333
<i>♪ That I ever wanted more ♪</i>

07:29.416 --> 07:33.833
<i>♪ Than to never feel</i>
<i>The breaking apart ♪</i>

07:33.916 --> 07:36.666
<i>♪ My pictures of you ♪</i>

07:38.333 --> 07:41.958
Well, proud papa is off to see
my baby girl do that thing

07:42.041 --> 07:44.833
that is usually the biggest
mistake of people's lives.

07:44.916 --> 07:46.666
She'll be so happy
her father is there.

07:46.750 --> 07:51.000
Oh, God. You can't just do that
to a person.

07:51.083 --> 07:52.166
[Herschel] Armageddon.

07:52.250 --> 07:53.375
You forgot to say knock-knock.

07:53.458 --> 07:55.500
[Herschel] No, real Armageddon.

07:55.583 --> 07:57.833
It's happening
at the Dietel County Fair.

07:57.916 --> 07:59.166
Dorothy needs help.

07:59.250 --> 08:01.125
She can't hold back
the Candlemaker.

08:01.208 --> 08:04.291
And what, pray tell,
is the Candlemaker?

08:04.375 --> 08:05.833
[Cliff] It's everything Chief
warned us about

08:05.916 --> 08:07.958
when he warned us
about Dorothy.

08:08.041 --> 08:10.166
[Herschel] He's wreaking havoc
and now the Chief's dying.

08:10.250 --> 08:11.500
And nobody can find him.

08:11.583 --> 08:14.500
And all of humanity's
about to go up in wax.

08:14.583 --> 08:15.666
We're on our way.

08:15.750 --> 08:17.041
Hurry!

08:18.833 --> 08:20.916
What, I can't lead a mission?

08:21.375 --> 08:22.500
Okay.

08:23.500 --> 08:25.000
-I'm in.
-Me too.

08:25.083 --> 08:26.541
You think Flit
can get us there?

08:26.625 --> 08:28.666
Flit's in. So am I.

08:30.166 --> 08:33.083
Well, I'm out.
I wanna see my daughter
get married.

08:33.166 --> 08:35.500
If it's the end of the world,
there won't be a wedding.

08:35.583 --> 08:37.041
If it's the end
of the world,

08:37.125 --> 08:39.791
I deserve to spend it
with my family.

08:39.875 --> 08:41.958
What the hell are we?

08:42.041 --> 08:44.041
For as long as
I can remember,

08:44.125 --> 08:47.333
no one out there
has given a damn about us.

08:49.791 --> 08:51.708
-We're all we have.
-So that's it?

08:51.791 --> 08:54.791
-Chief wins again?
-[Vic] This isn't
about the Chief.

08:54.875 --> 08:56.000
This is about Dorothy.

08:56.083 --> 08:58.041
And for me, it's about Clara.

08:58.833 --> 08:59.958
I have a daughter too!

09:00.041 --> 09:02.291
He's responsible for the life
he fucked up.

09:02.375 --> 09:05.416
I'm responsible for the life
I fucked up.

09:05.500 --> 09:07.250
I'm going to repair mine.

09:07.333 --> 09:10.000
If you want to be the man
your daughter
expects you to be,

09:10.083 --> 09:13.708
then you'll help
an 11-year-old girl
whose life is in danger.

09:15.666 --> 09:17.083
[Bump]<i> Hi, you've reached</i>

09:17.166 --> 09:18.958
<i>Salty Bumps'</i>
<i>bar and restaurant</i>

09:19.041 --> 09:20.625
<i>and tackle shop.</i>

09:20.708 --> 09:22.208
<i>-Our operating hours</i>
<i>are 8:00 a.m. to 2:00 a.m.</i>
-Fuck! Fuck! Fuck! Fuck!

09:22.291 --> 09:23.375
Fuck you, Bump.

09:23.458 --> 09:25.750
<i>-Closed on Sundays for Jesus.</i>
-[tone beeps]

09:25.833 --> 09:30.750
Uh, hi, Clara, it's your
fucking Father of the Year.

09:30.833 --> 09:34.750
Something's come up
and I'm not sure

09:34.833 --> 09:36.916
I understand myself, but...

09:37.000 --> 09:40.708
I might have to miss
the wedding.

09:40.791 --> 09:43.875
I'm sorry.

09:44.000 --> 09:46.625
And I know, I'm the last guy
you want to hear
another promise from,

09:46.708 --> 09:50.125
but I promise to be there
to welcome my first
and only grandchild.

09:50.208 --> 09:51.708
-I mean it.
-[tone beeps]

09:59.875 --> 10:02.000
-[thuds]
-Oh, I'm a fucking loser.

10:04.541 --> 10:07.166
[carnival music playing]

10:14.958 --> 10:15.958
[Miranda] Thanks, Flit.

10:16.041 --> 10:17.625
[Larry] What the hell
happened here?

10:23.708 --> 10:26.000
Okay. So,

10:26.083 --> 10:29.833
we have teleported up
Walt Disney's asshole.

10:30.250 --> 10:31.625
Now what?

10:31.708 --> 10:33.875
We find Niles, we find Dorothy
and we get the hell
out of here.

10:33.958 --> 10:36.458
Yeah, good luck with that.

10:36.541 --> 10:39.875
What the fuck kind of
Mike Tyson shit
happened to you?

10:42.250 --> 10:43.458
[panting]

10:43.541 --> 10:45.375
You can hold it back.

10:48.208 --> 10:49.583
Concentrate.

10:49.666 --> 10:51.833
You have to concentrate.

10:51.916 --> 10:55.458
[Candlemaker]<i> The time</i>
<i>for concentration</i>
<i>is over, girl.</i>

10:55.541 --> 10:57.083
<i>I am here.</i>

10:57.833 --> 10:59.916
<i>And so are your friends.</i>

11:00.000 --> 11:03.041
Good. Then they'll stop you.

11:03.125 --> 11:05.916
Forget the girl,
save yourselves.

11:06.000 --> 11:09.083
The Candlemaker's hijacked
that little shit's imagination,

11:09.166 --> 11:12.000
summoned imaginary friends
to do its bidding.

11:12.083 --> 11:14.708
Imaginary friends?
Like the Spider?

11:14.791 --> 11:17.291
"Like the Spider," he says...

11:17.375 --> 11:22.958
You clueless pack of twats
have no idea
what we're up against.

11:23.041 --> 11:25.416
Our imaginary friends.

11:28.958 --> 11:30.833
He's behind me, isn't he?

11:30.916 --> 11:32.333
-[puppet laughs]
-[Kipling groans]

11:32.416 --> 11:35.583
Your imaginary friend
is a Punch and Judy puppet?

11:35.666 --> 11:37.541
It was the 15th century.

11:37.625 --> 11:41.083
We didn't have
Bugs cunting Bunny.

11:50.708 --> 11:52.333
-He's gone.
-What the fuck?

11:52.416 --> 11:54.875
[Larry] For the first time,
I actually agree with Cliff.

11:54.958 --> 11:56.291
What the fuck?

11:56.375 --> 11:58.666
Look, Kipling can worry
about himself.

11:58.750 --> 12:00.875
We need to find Niles,
and fast.

12:02.000 --> 12:03.208
Let's split up.

12:04.708 --> 12:08.083
We're gonna find Niles
and we're gonna
kill that fucker dead.

12:08.166 --> 12:10.375
You hear me? Fucking fuck!

12:10.458 --> 12:12.416
[Larry] It's funny.
I never had
an imaginary friend.

12:12.500 --> 12:15.791
That is the saddest thing
I have ever heard.

12:19.708 --> 12:21.000
[gasps]

12:21.916 --> 12:24.250
[alarm bell ringing]

12:27.208 --> 12:29.083
What's wrong? What's happening?

12:29.166 --> 12:31.416
Sorry, the line went down.

12:32.125 --> 12:33.708
[electricity crackles]

12:34.625 --> 12:36.791
Why did you go
to the fairground?

12:36.875 --> 12:38.833
Dorothy is not our friend.

12:38.916 --> 12:41.583
You pulled the alarm
to question me?

12:42.791 --> 12:45.041
My job is to keep us
moving forward.

12:45.625 --> 12:47.333
That means making amends.

12:47.416 --> 12:50.708
Even Jane would think
before doing some
stupid shit like that.

12:50.791 --> 12:54.333
Amends with that thing up there
that killed some of our own?

12:54.416 --> 12:56.541
By the way, where is Jane?

12:56.625 --> 13:00.500
Maybe she's with Lucy Fugue
or Scarlet Harlot.

13:00.583 --> 13:01.916
They're missing too.

13:04.166 --> 13:08.333
Have any of you asked yourself
if this is what the girl wants?

13:10.041 --> 13:11.083
Hm?

13:11.833 --> 13:15.125
Do you even know
what Kay wants?

13:16.708 --> 13:18.875
Because I do.

13:18.958 --> 13:22.583
Tell you what,
you little doggies
keep yapping at each other.

13:23.583 --> 13:24.833
I have things to do.

13:24.916 --> 13:27.625
[alarm continues ringing]

13:40.500 --> 13:41.708
<i>Mademoiselle</i> Roxy?

13:41.791 --> 13:46.291
Hello, my starlet,
rosy cheeks Rita.

13:46.375 --> 13:48.916
[laughs] Look at you.

13:49.000 --> 13:50.500
How long's it been?

13:50.583 --> 13:53.000
-Ninety years.
-Wow.

13:53.083 --> 13:55.750
Well, I'd say we've both
held up pretty well.

13:55.833 --> 13:59.083
Am I still all the things
you aspired to?

14:22.166 --> 14:25.416
-[Dr. Cowboy] Howdy, partner!
-[arm cannon whirring]

14:26.583 --> 14:28.166
Dr. Cowboy?

14:29.125 --> 14:30.833
Well, I'll be gosh darned

14:30.916 --> 14:33.375
if you don't look tougher
than nails in that get-up.

14:33.458 --> 14:35.250
You're not Dr. Cowboy.
You can't be.

14:35.333 --> 14:38.208
Did you, uh...
You make all that yourself?

14:39.708 --> 14:42.416
What is that? Aluminum foil?

14:43.625 --> 14:44.583
Not another step.

14:44.666 --> 14:47.583
Oh, I remember this game.

14:47.666 --> 14:49.416
[Rita] What's going on here?

14:49.500 --> 14:53.666
I assume you're going to,
what, attack me?

14:53.750 --> 14:55.833
Try to rip me limb from limb?

14:55.916 --> 14:57.791
I feel I should warn you.

14:57.875 --> 15:00.833
I have certain abilities now,

15:00.916 --> 15:03.500
abilities I didn't possess
as a child.

15:04.833 --> 15:07.208
Stretchy abilities.

15:07.291 --> 15:09.750
Blobby abilities.

15:09.833 --> 15:11.416
They're really quite something.

15:11.500 --> 15:13.416
Attack you? Oh!

15:13.500 --> 15:17.541
I have something
much better planned.

15:17.625 --> 15:20.416
I'm afraid running
isn't an option, dear.

15:24.625 --> 15:25.875
Whenever you're ready.

15:28.916 --> 15:30.833
-Draw!
-[sonic wave blasts]

15:30.916 --> 15:32.916
Oh! You got me.

15:33.000 --> 15:35.750
[chuckles] But you were
always a good shot, Vic.

15:35.833 --> 15:37.625
[Dr. Cowboy panting]

15:37.708 --> 15:40.750
Plus, all I got is beakers.

15:43.375 --> 15:44.875
[grunts]

15:44.958 --> 15:47.041
This is it
for Dr. Cowboy, Vic.

15:48.708 --> 15:50.416
Everything's so pale.

15:52.208 --> 15:53.291
So pale.

16:02.875 --> 16:04.791
[arm cannon powers up]

16:07.500 --> 16:08.416
How are you still here?

16:08.500 --> 16:10.666
Well, I reckon
it's on account of me

16:10.750 --> 16:12.833
being in your imagination.

16:12.916 --> 16:15.625
Besides, you and I
need to talk, partner.

16:18.291 --> 16:22.333
I understand you're
having female problems.

16:28.583 --> 16:31.333
-[Roxy] Ready?
-We'll see.

16:31.416 --> 16:33.875
Then a one and a two and a...

16:34.250 --> 16:35.250
Oh!

16:35.333 --> 16:38.291
Not bad, kid. You still got it.

16:40.625 --> 16:44.833
Chief? Dorothy? Hello?

16:46.750 --> 16:48.250
It's all good.

16:50.000 --> 16:53.291
We'll find shithead
and his kid and we'll split.

16:53.375 --> 16:56.208
I might even make it
to the wedding in time
to see Clara toss the--

16:56.291 --> 16:57.750
[grunts]

16:57.833 --> 17:01.375
Get off me.
Get off me!

17:01.458 --> 17:03.375
-Jesus?
-Hey, Cliffy,
you piece of shit.

17:03.458 --> 17:06.125
What the fuck?
You were my imaginary friend

17:06.208 --> 17:08.416
for, like, half a summer
at Bible Camp!

17:08.500 --> 17:10.291
Yeah. And then
you forsook my ass.

17:10.375 --> 17:11.625
[Cliff] Wait! Jesus.

17:11.708 --> 17:13.500
I come in peace.

17:13.583 --> 17:15.208
Maybe we could talk this out?

17:15.291 --> 17:16.916
You think I give
a French fried titty fuck

17:17.000 --> 17:19.291
about anything
you have to say
right now, Cliff?

17:19.375 --> 17:21.000
I'm here to end you.

17:22.458 --> 17:24.708
[Cliff screams]

17:41.666 --> 17:43.333
["If You Could
Read My Mind" playing]

17:43.416 --> 17:45.708
-Where do you want it?
-Uh...

17:46.583 --> 17:49.125
This works, I think.

17:51.666 --> 17:55.583
<i>♪ About a ghost</i>
<i>From a wishing well ♪</i>

17:55.666 --> 17:58.583
<i>♪ In a castle dark ♪</i>

17:58.666 --> 18:00.750
You wanna take a break
and fool around?

18:00.833 --> 18:02.458
Uh, kind of.

18:04.833 --> 18:07.708
<i>♪ You know that ghost is me ♪</i>

18:08.916 --> 18:12.791
<i>♪ And I will never</i>
<i>Be set free ♪</i>

18:12.875 --> 18:15.208
<i>♪ As long as I'm a ghost... ♪</i>

18:15.291 --> 18:16.833
What?

18:16.916 --> 18:20.000
I'm just thinking back
to that girl I met at the diner
a couple years ago.

18:20.083 --> 18:22.291
The one who went bananas
when I touched her cheek.

18:23.208 --> 18:26.416
Oh, I hear
she's a sex maniac now.

18:27.166 --> 18:28.958
-Mm-hm.
-Mm.

18:29.041 --> 18:33.000
<i>♪ Just like a paperback novel ♪</i>

18:33.083 --> 18:36.791
<i>♪ The kind</i>
<i>The drugstore sells ♪</i>

18:38.125 --> 18:39.458
Can't believe
we're doing this.

18:41.041 --> 18:43.083
I know you keep saying that,

18:43.833 --> 18:45.708
so I'll believe it, eventually.

18:45.791 --> 18:47.250
Don't put that on me, okay?

18:50.000 --> 18:53.166
<i>♪ And you won't read</i>
<i>That book again ♪</i>

18:53.250 --> 18:55.458
I'm not.

18:55.541 --> 19:00.000
I'm just not as sure
about everything
I do like you.

19:00.916 --> 19:02.291
Okay?

19:02.375 --> 19:03.458
I have...

19:04.375 --> 19:06.333
things I...

19:06.416 --> 19:09.166
have to think of before
I make a decision like this.

19:09.250 --> 19:10.583
Look...

19:10.666 --> 19:14.333
I know you didn't have
the happiest of homes
growing up.

19:14.416 --> 19:17.958
And I know you need
your alone time to sketch

19:18.041 --> 19:21.833
and talk to yourself
or whatever.

19:21.916 --> 19:25.166
But I want you to know that
we'll make this work.

19:26.458 --> 19:27.583
I know.

19:30.750 --> 19:32.875
You think we can actually
get this place
set up by Saturday?

19:32.958 --> 19:34.416
What's this "we" business?

19:34.500 --> 19:38.041
I'm sorry I can't take a day.
I gotta be seen
